<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="NAME"
>NAME <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<p>Test::LectroTest::RegressionTesting - How to do regression testing (for free!)</p>

<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="SYNOPSIS"
>SYNOPSIS <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<pre class="sh_perl">    use Test::LectroTest
        regressions =&#62; &#34;regressions.txt&#34;;

    # -- OR --

    use Test::LectroTest
        playback_failures =&#62; &#34;regression_suite_for_my_module.txt&#34;,
        record_failures   =&#62; &#34;failures_in_the_field.txt&#34;;

    # -- OR --

    use Test::LectroTest::Compat
        regressions =&#62; &#34;regressions.txt&#34;;

    # -- OR --

    use Test::LectroTest::Compat
        playback_failures =&#62; &#34;regression_suite_for_my_module.txt&#34;,
        record_failures   =&#62; &#34;failures_in_the_field.txt&#34;;</pre>

<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="DESCRIPTION"
>DESCRIPTION <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<p>Say that LectroTest uncovers a bug in your software by finding a random test case that proves one of your properties to be false. If you apply a fix for the bug, how can you be sure that LectroTest will re-test the property using the exact same test case that &#34;broke&#34; it before, just to be certain the bug really is fixed? And how can you be sure that future changes to your code will not reintroduce the same bug without your knowing it?</p>

<p>For situations like these, LectroTest can record failure-causing test cases to a file, and it can play those test cases back as part of its normal testing strategy.</p>

<p>The easiest way to take advantage of this feature is to set the <i>regressions</i> parameter when you <code>use</code> <a href="/~tmoertel/Test-LectroTest-0.3600/lib/Test/LectroTest.pm" class="podlinkpod"
>Test::LectroTest</a> or <a href="/~tmoertel/Test-LectroTest-0.3600/lib/Test/LectroTest/Compat.pm" class="podlinkpod"
>Test::LectroTest::Compat</a>:</p>

<pre class="sh_perl">    use Test::LectroTest
        regressions =&#62; &#34;regressions.txt&#34;;</pre>

<p>This tells LectroTest to use the file &#34;regressions.txt&#34; for both recording and playing back failures. If you want to record and play back from separate files, use the <i>record_failures</i> and <i>playback_failures</i> options:</p>

<pre class="sh_perl">    use Test::LectroTest::Compat
        playback_failures =&#62; &#34;regression_suite_for_my_module.txt&#34;,
        record_failures   =&#62; &#34;failures_in_the_field.txt&#34;;</pre>

<p>Here is how it works:</p>

<ol>
<li>When testing a property named <i>N</i>, LectroTest will check for a play-back file. If the file exists, LectroTest will search it for test cases associated with <i>N</i>. If any such test cases exist, LectroTest will play them back <i>before</i> and <i>in addition to</i> performing the usual, random testing of the property.</li>

<li>When performing the usual, random testing of a property named <i>N</i>, if a failure occurs (i.e., LectroTest finds a counterexample), LectroTest will record the test case that caused the failure to the recording file, associating the test case with the name <i>N</i>.</li>
</ol>

<p><b>NOTE:</b> If you pass any of the recording or playback parameters to <a href="/~tmoertel/Test-LectroTest-0.3600/lib/Test/LectroTest/Compat.pm" class="podlinkpod"
>Test::LectroTest::Compat</a>, you must have version 0.3500 or greater of Test::LectroTest installed. (Module authors, update your modules&#39; build dependencies accordingly.) The <a href="/~tmoertel/Test-LectroTest-0.3600/lib/Test/LectroTest.pm" class="podlinkpod"
>Test::LectroTest</a> module itself, however, has always ignored unfamiliar parameters, and thus these options are backward compatible with older versions.</p>

<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="SEE_ALSO"
>SEE ALSO <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<p><a href="/~tmoertel/Test-LectroTest-0.3600/lib/Test/LectroTest.pm" class="podlinkpod"
>Test::LectroTest</a> gives a quick overview of automatic, specification-based testing with LectroTest. This module accepts failure recording and play-back options.</p>

<p><a href="/~tmoertel/Test-LectroTest-0.3600/lib/Test/LectroTest/Compat.pm" class="podlinkpod"
>Test::LectroTest::Compat</a> lets you mix LectroTest with the popular family of <a href="/perldoc?Test%3A%3ABuilder" class="podlinkpod"
>Test::Builder</a>-based modules such as <a href="/perldoc?Test%3A%3ASimple" class="podlinkpod"
>Test::Simple</a> and <a href="/perldoc?Test%3A%3AMore" class="podlinkpod"
>Test::More</a>. This module accepts failure recording and play-back options.</p>

